231/* umul_hi(h, x, y) puts in h the high part of x*y */
232#ifdef HAVE_MULX_U64
233#include <immintrin.h>
234#define umul_hi(h, x, y) _mulx_u64 (x, y, (unsigned long long *) &h)
235#else
236#define umul_hi(h, x, y) \
237 do { \
238 mp_limb_t _l; \
239 umul_ppmm (h, _l, x, y); \
240 } while (0)
241#endif
242
243/* given 2^62 <= d < 2^64, put in r an approximation of
244 s = floor(2^96/sqrt(r)) - 2^64, with r <= s <= r + 15 */
245#define __gmpfr_invsqrt_limb_approx(r, d) \
246 do { \
247 mp_limb_t _d, _i, _v0, _e0, _d37, _v1, _e1, _h, _v2, _e2; \
248 _d = (d); \
249 _i = (_d >> 54) - 256; \
250 /* i = d10 - 256 */ \
251 _v0 = T[_i]; \
252 _d37 = 1 + (_d >> 27); \
253 _e0 = T3[_i] * _d37; \
254 /* the value (_v0 << 57) - _e0 is less than 2^61 */ \
255 _v1 = (_v0 << 11) + (((_v0 << 57) - _e0) >> 47); \
256 _e1 = - _v1 * _v1 * _d37; \
257 umul_hi (_h, _v1, _e1); \
258 /* _h = floor(e_1*v_1/2^64) */ \
259 _v2 = (_v1 << 10) + (_h >> 6); \
260 umul_hi (_h, _v2 * _v2, _d); \
261 /* in _h + 2, one +1 accounts for the lower neglected part of */ \
262 /* v2^2*d. the other +1 is to compute ceil((h+1)/2) */ \
263 _e2 = (MPFR_LIMB_ONE << 61) - ((_h + 2) >> 1); \
264 _h = _v2 * _e2; \
265 (r) = (_v2 << 33) + (_h >> 29); \
266 } while (0)
267
268/* given 2^62 <= d < 2^64, return a 32-bit approximation r of
269 sqrt(2^126/d) */
270#define __gmpfr_invsqrt_halflimb_approx(r, d) \
271 do { \
272 mp_limb_t _d, _i, _v0, _e0, _d37, _v1, _e1, _h; \
273 _d = (d); \
274 _i = (_d >> 54) - 256; \
275 /* i = d10 - 256 */ \
276 _v0 = T[_i]; \
277 _d37 = 1 + (_d >> 27); \
278 _e0 = T3[_i] * _d37; \
279 /* the value (_v0 << 57) - _e0 is less than 2^61 */ \
280 _v1 = (_v0 << 11) + (((_v0 << 57) - _e0) >> 47); \
281 _e1 = - _v1 * _v1 * _d37; \
282 umul_hi (_h, _v1, _e1); \
283 /* _h = floor(e_1*v_1/2^64) */ \
284 (r) = (_v1 << 10) + (_h >> 6); \
285 } while (0)
286
287/* given 2^62 <= n < 2^64, put in s an approximation of sqrt(2^64*n),
288 with: s <= floor(sqrt(2^64*u)) <= s + 7 */
289#define __gmpfr_sqrt_limb_approx(s, n) \
290 do { \
291 mp_limb_t _n, _x, _y, _z, _t; \
292 _n = (n); \
293 __gmpfr_invsqrt_halflimb_approx (_x, _n); \
294 MPFR_ASSERTD(_x < MPFR_LIMB_ONE << 32); \
295 /* x has 32 bits, and is near (by below) sqrt(2^126/n) */ \
296 _y = (_x * (_n >> 31)) >> 32; \
297 MPFR_ASSERTD(_y < MPFR_LIMB_ONE << 32); \
298 /* y is near (by below) sqrt(n) */ \
299 _z = _n - _y * _y; \
300 /* reduce _z so that _z <= 2*_y */ \
301 /* the maximal value of _z is 2*(2^32-1) */ \
302 while (_z > 2 * ((MPFR_LIMB_ONE << 32) - 1)) \
303 { \
304 _z -= (_y + _y) + 1; \
305 _y ++; \
306 } \
307 /* now z <= 2*(2^32-1): one reduction is enough */ \
308 if (_z > _y + _y) \
309 { \
310 _z -= (_y + _y) + 1; \
311 _y ++; \
312 } \
313 /* _x * _z should be < 2^64 */ \
314 _t = (_x * _z) >> 32; \
315 (s) = (_y << 32) + _t; \
316 } while (0)
317
318/* given 2^62 <= u < 2^64, put in s the value floor(sqrt(2^64*u)),
319 and in rh in rl the remainder: 2^64*u - s^2 = 2^64*rh + rl, with
320 2^64*rh + rl <= 2*s, and in invs the approximation of 2^96/sqrt(u) */
321#define __gmpfr_sqrt_limb(s, rh, rl, invs, u) \
322 do { \
323 mp_limb_t _u, _invs, _r, _h, _l; \
324 _u = (u); \
325 __gmpfr_invsqrt_limb_approx (_invs, _u); \
326 umul_hi (_h, _invs, _u); \
327 _r = _h + _u; \
328 /* make sure _r has its most significant bit set */ \
329 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY(_r < MPFR_LIMB_HIGHBIT)) \
330 _r = MPFR_LIMB_HIGHBIT; \
331 /* we know _r <= sqrt(2^64*u) <= _r + 16 */ \
332 umul_ppmm (_h, _l, _r, _r); \
333 sub_ddmmss (_h, _l, _u, 0, _h, _l); \
334 /* now h:l <= 30*_r */ \
335 MPFR_ASSERTD(_h < 30); \
336 if (_h >= 16) \
337 { /* subtract 16r+64 to h:l, add 8 to _r */ \
338 sub_ddmmss (_h, _l, _h, _l, _r >> 60, _r << 4); \
339 sub_ddmmss (_h, _l, _h, _l, 0, 64); \
340 _r += 8; \
341 } \
342 if (_h >= 8) \
343 { /* subtract 8r+16 to h:l, add 4 to _r */ \
344 sub_ddmmss (_h, _l, _h, _l, _r >> 61, _r << 3); \
345 sub_ddmmss (_h, _l, _h, _l, 0, 16); \
346 _r += 4; \
347 } \
348 if (_h >= 4) \
349 { /* subtract 4r+4 to h:l, add 2 to _r */ \
350 sub_ddmmss (_h, _l, _h, _l, _r >> 62, _r << 2); \
351 sub_ddmmss (_h, _l, _h, _l, 0, 4); \
352 _r += 2; \
353 } \
354 while (_h > 1 || ((_h == 1) && (_l > 2 * _r))) \
355 { /* subtract 2r+1 to h:l, add 1 to _r */ \
356 sub_ddmmss (_h, _l, _h, _l, _r >> 63, (_r << 1) + 1); \
357 _r ++; \
358 } \
359 (s) = _r; \
360 (rh) = _h; \
361 (rl) = _l; \
362 (invs) = _invs; \
363 } while (0)
364
365#endif /* GMP_NUMB_BITS == 64 */
